**Narrative:**  
Disney is the ultimate symbol of innocence, magic, and family entertainment. Criticism of Disney is conspiracy thinking by sick people.

**Reality:**

In April 2026, **27 crew members** from cruise ships were arrested in the port of San Diego for possession, receipt, and distribution of child pornography.  
**Ten of them worked directly for Disney Cruise Line.**

Ten.

Disney — the company that has positioned itself for decades as the safest, most child-friendly entertainment empire in the world — had ten employees on one of its ships distributing child pornography.

This is not “a few bad apples.” This is a structural problem.

The mainstream media? Almost complete silence.  
Any other major company would have been front-page news for weeks. At Disney? A small article and then quickly on to the next feel-good story.

This fits a larger, ugly pattern: major institutions (Disney, Hollywood, churches, sports clubs, elites) that sell a pure, innocent image, while the reality behind the scenes is often extremely dark.

